name: protein-glutamate O-methyltransferase
reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + protein L-glutamate = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + protein L-glutamate methyl ester [RN:R02623]
comment: Forms ester groups with L-glutamate residues in a number of membrane proteins.

orthologs.K13924: two-component system, chemotaxis family, CheB/CheR fusion protein

references.title: Purification and characterization of Bacillus subtilis methyl-accepting chemotaxis protein methyltransferase II.
Isolation of glutamic acid methyl ester from an Escherichia coli membrane protein involved in chemotaxis.
Purification and characterization of the S-adenosylmethionine:glutamyl methyltransferase that modifies membrane chemoreceptor proteins in bacteria.
Identification of a protein methyltransferase as the cheR gene product in the bacterial sensing system.
references.journal: Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U. S. A. 74 (1977) 533-7.
